> e

I am in the dining room, which is slightly higher than the foyer, due to the hotel having been built on the slope of the mountain. Furnished in typical Carpathian style, though the benches and tables are crudely hewn but very functional. If it were not for the disquieting feeling of gloom about the place, one could quite readily assume it to be and English coach house as found on the Canterbury turnpike...

Several other weary travellers are here already, dining on extremely wholesome fare.
Very appetizing!!!
Ah! There is an empty table beside me.
> sit

> sit

I am seated and noticing a menu, pick it up.... what luck, it is in English!
> read menu

> read menu

Ah! Compact but I'm sure, sustaining!

The innkeeper's wife appears and comes to my table:
"Good evening mein herr. Our fare is simple, but goot! What would you wish to eat?"

> lamb

> lamb

"Ya! The lamb iss goot!" She says and disappears into the kitchen, returning shortly with the lamb stew. I eat my meal eagerly as the day's journey has created rather an appetite!

She returns as I finsih, with a slightly anxious air about her... I sense her eagerness to clear the room so she may retire to her bed. What is it about this place?....it seems so..... oppressive...."
"Would you wish a drink? The wine is chilled, or perhaps just some water? Or maybe you require nothing to drink?"
> water

> water

"Cool spring water sir, " She replies, "iss goot.... does not jumble the brain!"
I drink the sparkling water. I must admit it has a subtle purity about it....

Two children appear.
Probably offspring of the innkeeper's. There is a flurry of activity as they clear the tables.

Again, I sense an urgency in their behaviour...most odd.
They quickly scurry off, leaving me alone in the room.

