> sleep

> sleep

I make for the bed and pull back the sheets. My weary limbs were never more grateful to find a resting place.Within moments I am asleep...
Dreams..images, flash through my mind's eye. Sleep knows no passage of time..is it a moment or a night? In the half-world between waking and slumber, there are...sounds.

I hear..footsteps.
Not friendly, but...menacing!
My inner self sees terror such as only the mind can create!

I see a cloaked figure. A tall, slender, yet powerful image.
I look to his face.
Heaven help me... he has no face!!
Just raw burned flesh!! In an instant he..it changes. The flesh contorts into a new degree of malevolence... now a hideous creature with the form of a wolf's head!

It towers above me! I smell it's putrid breath..so close..burning red eyes sear into the very inner being of my mind...
A loud scream destroys my mental focus..my brain cannot cope...
This apparition drips fetid blood onto my face..evil exudes from every pore of it's vile being!! It gets closer!! I may never awake from this bizarre haunting!!

Suddenly.......a howling!! Such a howling that turns my blood to ice!! My heart has surely stopped..I hear a demented laugh...flapping of wings???
When will my torment end?
The appartition gets closer still and without warning...lifts off the ground, levitating above me.
The face changes to a....writing mass of maggot eaten flesh!!
Will this ever end?? Then.......... this horror rises rapidly to the roof!

It hits the roof with a sickly crunch..again that laugh! Bone, blood and small white worms fall down on me like the devil's rain....please deliver me!

......I awake!!
What an awful dream! I sit down and try to compose myself.
Wait!....What is this......what is going on? I hear a distant scream and yes! As in my dream, beating wings!
God! What a terrifying sound!
