The Castle!!

What an awesome building. It's black presence looms above me. But it is far from immaculate. Indeed it is in severe dis-repair. There is a....neglected air about the place, and a.....gloom of immense proportions. The coach slows as it enters the courtyard, then stops. I shed the blankets then alight. The coach leaves by whence it came. The driver, when outside the castle walls, pulls the huge oak doors shut. I hear a latch being tripped.....

I now stand alone!

