I climb the staircase. A tremour of panic rips through me! Why has this trip been so demanding? I sense.... a black gloom...a despair of the soul!
I am at last in the entrance porch to the castle!
A gloomy portico! A heavy door bars my way North. This massive portal is mounted in an equally immense frame.

> examine frame

> examine frame

A sturdy structure indeed!
On it is mounted a bronze bat, now blackened with age.

> examine bat

> examine bat

Beautifully crafted...but with such infernal features! The mouth also seems too large.
> feel mouth

> feel mouth

Ah! There is a button here! I press it and hear, deep within, a bell.
I hear no one approach, yet there is a ponderous turning of locks and the door swings open....
I know not why I should dread this moment but I do! This dark, damp mausoleum exudes a vileness which I would rather avoid, but my duty is to give council to the Count, so I must. I look into the now open portal.

Count Dracula stands before me! My blood freezes! He is an immense presence both physically, and in spirit...I am dwarfed, diminished! Much taller than i imagined, he has the pallor of death about him and yet almost glows with a malignant energy..

"Welcome to my house. Enter freely and of your own will."

His voice is cultured but lacks any humanity whatsoever!
He stands aside to allow me access.

I feel that I have no choice, so I enter. No sooner have I done so, than he seizes my hand to welcome me. His strength is awesome! His handshake has surely broken my bones!

"Come my friend, you must be tired. Let me show you your room, where you may rest. Tomorrow evening we will talk."

He leads me through corridors and rooms. I am totally lost! He opens a door and I enter.

"Sleep well my friend!" So saying he shuts the door and is gone.
But not before locking it!

I fall to the bed exhausted and am immediately asleep.

It is light!
I cannot believe the night has gone. My watch indicates late afternoon! I quickly rise and dress.

