The door is unlocked and the count comes in.

"Hello my sleepy friend. I trust you slept well? Come! Let me take you to the drawing room where we have much to dicuss. Ah! A thing of vanity we do not need here!"
He takes the polished tray. We walk across the corridor to the drawing room.
"Be seated my friend."
I do not argue the point!

The count looks at me.
"Mr Harker. You have the details of the property that you have purchased for me."
I reply that I have, and glady hand them over to hasten my departure. Then my heart sinks.
"I will require you to stay on a while, there are other services I wish of you."

We talk into the night on many topics, about his new mansion in England, and the surrounding geography. He has an immense knowledge of every subject, yet he soaks up everything I tell him like a sponge!.... He frightens me!

"And so, you do not see a problem with the transporting of fifty boxes of my homeland soil to England?"

I confirm this to him.

"Then I will bid you goodnight. By the way, you have limited access to the castle. Please respect my wishes. There are good reasons for locked doors."

Then he rises and leaves. I feel as If I had been released from a trance! My mind is made up. I have to get away from here!

