Ah! A letter for me. I take the letter and open it.
It is from my friend Jonathan Harker, in Transylvania. It reads;

"My dear friend, I write of impending doom. Believe me! I cannot describe the terror of late, but it is imperative to locate 50 boxes of soil being imported in to England. You must discover a means of preventing their use by the undead. I know not how, only that you must! I am weak, I will write again soon. P.S. Visit my company in Stratford...ask for Hawkins. They may have more news. Regards, J.H.

Well, I know he is serious. I must plan to do as he asks. Although I confess I don't understand it!
