I am in a hidden, overgrown mausoleum, which is in the gardens of the house. It is derelict now. Lumps of stonework lie scattered among the moss and grass on the floor.
He is here in the last box! God give me strength for what I have to do! I plunge the stake into his heart. His eyes spring open! His vile mouth gasps and his obscene body writhes! Blood pumps over his chest and runs from his nose and the corner of his mouth! He snarls and hisses, blood splattering over me!

I approach my next task with every nerve in my body screaming! I swallow hard, and quickly raise the heavy knife and bring it down, Thwack! Across his throat! He continues to writhe! I bring it down again and again. Then I adopt a sawing action to complete this gruesome duty.
At last it is free! I grasp it and fling it across the room!
Immediately the body decomposes into a foul pool of putrification...where the head landed I see a glint of light. I stagger across to the wall and push. A stone panel falls away and I emerge into a hazy, sunlit afternoon in the overgrown garden......

I breathe in the fresh, sweet air, look at the fluffy clouds drifting lazily across the sky, and thank God it is over.......

Somewhere I hear a bird singing.

